title: SFH begins four-nation visit to Europe (with photo)
content_text:
p>
    The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, has embarked on the first 
    day of his four-nation visit to Europe, meeting Estonian government 
    officials in charge of health and social policy. Arriving at Tallinn this afternoon (May 13, Estonia time), Dr Chow met the 
    Estonian Minister of Social Affairs, Mr Hanno Pevkur, and his team to learn 
    about Estonia's healthcare system and the electronic health record (eHR)

about Estonia's healthcare system and the electronic health record (eHR) 
    system. Mr Pevkur introduced to Dr Chow the latest development of the eHR system in 
    Estonia. It was learnt that the Estonian government applied e-Government 
    services widely and that Estonia's healthcare system is built on the basis 
    of mandatory insurance, which in turn requires healthcare providers to 
    participate in eHR sharing. Dr Chow was told that the eHealth project in Estonia involved various 
    sectors of the community and the Ministry of Social Affairs took up the

sectors of the community and the Ministry of Social Affairs took up the 
    coordinating and directing role in implementing the project. Dr Chow said he hoped that Hong Kong could learn from Estonia the various 
    aspects of its eHR system including measures that have been adopted to 
    ensure data standardisation and interoperability among different healthcare 
    providers. During his two-day visit to Estonia, Dr Chow will call on the North Estonia 
    Medical Centre, the biggest hospital offering specialised medical treatment 
    in Northern Estonia, and the Estonia ICT Demo Centre, a not-for-profit

in Northern Estonia, and the Estonia ICT Demo Centre, a not-for-profit organisation promoting e-solutions to healthcare providers both domestically and internationally. Ends/Thursday, May 13, 2010
Issued at HKT 19:37
